{
  "message": "fuzz(extent-cache-concurrent): 15 structured seeds covering eviction,\nnamespaces, op-mix, and concurrency shapes\n\nfuzz_extent_cache_concurrent spawns 4 worker threads driving\nffs_extent::ExtentCache through random op streams (insert / lookup /\ninvalidate_range / invalidate_all / stats / reset_stats) and asserts\nfour invariants (geometry coverage, monotonic stats, post-\ninvalidate_all cleared state, post-reset stats counters). The\nexisting 3 ad-hoc seeds (basic, eviction_pressure, invalidate_all)\nleft most of the worker-mix phase space unexplored.\n\nAdds 15 seeds that explicitly target every interesting axis:\n\n  Capacity dimension:\n  * capacity=4 with rapid-fire inserts in every worker\n    (eviction storm \u2014 pins the entries-bounded-by-capacity invariant)\n  * capacity=16 balanced (every op type at least twice per worker)\n  * capacity=256 per-namespace inserts (no eviction expected)\n\n  Op-mix coverage:\n  * pure-lookup over a cold cache (every lookup misses)\n  * insert-then-lookup-same-range (must hit modulo concurrent races)\n  * insert + invalidate_range covering the same range\n  * cycles of insert + invalidate_all (I3 stress)\n  * stats-heavy with periodic reset_stats\n  * pure-invalidate ops on a cold cache (must be no-ops, never panic)\n  * single worker dominates (others empty \u2014 exercises asymmetric\n    chunk_len)\n\n  Cache-layout edge cases:\n  * overlapping inserts at the same logical_start with growing counts\n    (exercises overwrite/coalesce path)\n  * max-count (count=8) inserts in every worker\n  * mixed namespaces \u2014 every op rotates ns through 0..4\n  * unwritten=true on every insert (separate invalidation path)\n  * lookup boundaries (first / last / one-past / one-before of an\n    inserted range)\n\nValidated by a 16 s libFuzzer run: 14 959 executions over the new\ncorpus (each run spawns 4 worker threads + asserts post-workload\ninvariants, so throughput is single-digit-thousands), no crashes.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
